BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:mraDYhNIbYD1O7Ijh_tqy
SUMMARY:Singing Seattle: A Reading and Celebration
DTSTAMP:20260403T051040Z
DTSTART:20260402T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Singing Seattle: A Reading and Celebration \\nThree authors rea
	d poetry and creative nonfiction that speaks to our moment\\\, followed by
	 a Q&A and book signing. Samina Najmi reads from her debut memoir-in-essay
	s Sing Me A Circle: Love\\\, Loss\\\, and a Home in Time\\\, Lena Khalaf T
	uffaha from her award-winning poetry collection Something About Living\\\,
	 and Kalehua Kim from her debut poetry collection Mele. The readings will 
	be followed by a Q&A and book signing. \\nFree admission to this event is 
	made possible with support from 4Culture.\n\nhttps://hugohouse.org/event/_
	2026-04-02/\n\nFrom Hugo House
URL:https://hugohouse.org/event/_2026-04-02/
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:hugo-house
CATEGORIES:Hugo House
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
