BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ToJLB3VbtCCoLWwUeVohA
SUMMARY:Open Mic for Musicians
DTSTAMP:20260403T051040Z
DTSTART:20260417T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Hugo House Music Open Mic \\n \\nJoin us for Hugo House's first
	 ever music-forward open mic night centered on original work only\\\, no c
	overs. This event brings together musicians\\\, writers\\\, and hybrid per
	formers. With a limited lineup and a community-centered atmosphere\\\, eac
	h performance is given space to be fully experienced. Whether you're perfo
	rming or attending\\\, expect a engaging evening centered on creativity\\\
	, craft\\\, and connection. \\nEvent Overview \\n\\n20 total performers\\\
	, 10 pre-registered\\nPre-register here\\n10 day-of sign-ups (first come\\
	\, first served)\\nPerformance styles: Music\\\, poetry\\\, prose\\\, or h
	ybrid\\nAudience seating: Maximum capacity is 80\\n\\nSign-Ups & Check-In 
	\\n\\nPre-Registration opens April 1. Please follow this link to pre-regis
	ter \\nLimited to 10 spots\\nCheck-in required by 6:00 PM on event day\\nU
	nclaimed spots may be released\\n\\nDay-Of Sign-Ups \\n\\nOpen at 6:00 PM 
	(front desk)\\nClose at 6:50 PM or when full\\nFirst come\\\, first served
	\\n\\nPerformance Guidelines \\n\\n5-minute sets (includes setup + transit
	ions)\\n(Up to ~6 minutes max if needed)\\nSolo artists or duos preferred\
	\nOriginal work only\\\, no covers\\n\\nPerformance Overview \\n\\nKeep it
	 simple: No full bands\\\, drum kits\\\, loud electric setups\\\, or backi
	ng tracks.\\nBasic gear provided: Mics\\\, DI boxes\\\, stands\\\, and lim
	ited accessories—bring small extras if needed.\\nQuick sound checks only: 
	Levels are set fast and won’t be adjusted during the show.\\nBe ready: Pre
	p offstage\\\, keep setup minimal\\\, and be ready when called or risk los
	ing your spot.\\nStrict timing: Sets are enforced with a warning\; hosts m
	ay end performances if needed.\\nAccessible setup available: Flexible mic 
	options\\\, seating support\\\, and extra time on request.\\nBe respectful
	: Follow guidelines and support fellow performers and the audience.\\n\\nA
	ny additional questions? Email nat@hugohouse.org\n\nhttps://hugohouse.org/
	event/_2026-04-17/\n\nFrom Hugo House
URL:https://hugohouse.org/event/_2026-04-17/
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:hugo-house
CATEGORIES:Hugo House
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
